<HEADLINE> CPC Central Committee Hosts Lantern Festival Gathering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) hosted an evening party in the
Great Hall of the People in Beijing to celebrate the traditional
Chinese Lantern Festival.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 noted intellectuals attended the gathering along with
a number of CPC and state leaders, including CPC General Secretary
Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Liu Huaqing,
Hu Jintao and Wei Jianxing.
</P>
<P>
Participants spent a delightful evening sipping tea, watching
art performances and chatting in the hall decorated with colorful
lanterns.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, member of the Standing Committee of the CPC Central
Committee Politburo, offered festival greetings to the participants
and intellectuals throughout the nation on behalf of the CPC
central leadership.
</P>
<P>
Hu cited 1997 as a banner year in the history of the Party and
the country. He said that China successfully resumed the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong and noted the highly successful 15th
National Congress of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
China's economy has maintained a sound trend toward "high
growth and low inflation", said Hu. He thanked the country's
intellectuals for their contributions to the ongoing
reform, opening and modernization efforts.
</P>
<P>
Hu urged intellectuals to work hard to ensure the prosperity
and development of cultural pursuits and the advancement of the
great cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics
as the world enters the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Hu called for upholding the great banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory under the leadership of the CPC Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core.  
</P>
</TEXT>
