<HEADLINE> Shanghai Orphans Enjoy Happiness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 11 (Xinhua) -- A group of 40 adopted
disabled orphans and their foster families gathered today at a
restaurant in Shanghai to celebrate the last day of this year's
Spring Festival.
</P>
<P>
Chinese tradition calls for family members to gather for a
"reunion dinner" on the last day of Spring Festival with a good
end. The event enabled the orphans and their foster families to
enjoy precious family warmth.
</P>
<P>
The families have adopted handicapped orphans since May 1997
under the joint sponsorship of the Shanghai Municipal Civil
Administration Bureau, Xin Ming Evening News and Shanghai Charity
Fund.
</P>
<P>
The foster parents regard the disabled orphans as their own
children and have rendered loving care over the past nine months.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongfang, 45, a foster mother who used to work as a
kindergarten teacher, said: "I adopted an orphan because I know
that parental love overcomes loneliness."
</P>
<P>
The adopted children have undergone great change, with their
average heights increasing by 3.62 centimeters and weights by 1.1
kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Jingbo, deputy secretary of the Shanghai Charity Fund,
said that between 40-60 disabled orphans are expected to be
adopted in the first three months of 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
