<HEADLINE> Lebanon and Bulgaria To Strengthen Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, February 11 (Xinhua) - Lebanon will try to restore its
relations with its partners, especially with Bulgaria, Lebanese
Defense Minister Muhsin Dallul told a news conference Wednesday
at the end of his three-day official visit to Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, he discussed with his Bulgarian counterpart
the possibilities of training Lebanese military personnel at
Bulgarian higher military schools, and cooperation between the two
ministries in sports and recreation, Dallul said.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the Iraqi crisis, the Defense Minister said
Lebanon believes a diplomatic solution can be found through
dialogue, .
</P>
<P>
He expressed the same stand Monday following his talks on
bilateral relations and the situation in the Middle East with
Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan Kostov.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese Prime Minister is expected to visit Bulgaria soon
at the invitation of Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan Kostov, he
announced.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian Foreign Minister Nadezhda Mihailova and the ministers
of trade and of agriculture of the two countries are also expected
to exchange visits. 
