<HEADLINE> Spokesman: Iraqis Determined to Defend Country </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Iraq Wednesday stressed that
the Iraqi people are determined to maintain the integrity,
sovereignty and independence of their country.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi people are also ready to defend themselves against a
possible military attack launched by the United States, a
spokesman of the Ministry of Culture and Information told the
Iraqi News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman was commenting on a recent statement by British
Foreign Secretary Robin Cook, that any possible U.S. attack on
Iraq might lead to Iraq's partition which Britain would welcome.
</P>
<P>
Cook "expresses the odious strategy of partition which has been
championed by British imperialism in dealing with the Third World
nations over the last two centuries," the Iraqi spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"Cook seems to be still taking a pre-Second World War view of
his country's prestige and is still dreaming an effective colonial
role for it, forgetting that Britain no longer has a role in
international politics but a subordinate to the U.S.," he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Saad Qassem Hammoudi, chairman of the Arab and
International Committee of the Iraqi National Assembly, slammed
U.S. Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott for calling on jamming
Iraqi radio networks and addressing American radio transmissions
to the Iraqi people.
</P>
<P>
"We find it strange for a senior parliamentary official to talk
with such a logic which implies a trend hostile to the rights of
man and democracy simultaneously," Saad Hammoudi said.
</P>
<P>
This means that Lott is seeking to deny the human and sovereign
rights of the Iraqis to express views at home and attempting to
impose enemy's views on the Iraqi people, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
