<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's New Motor Vehicle Sales Up in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Canada's new motor vehicle
sales posted their strongest monthly gain of the year in December,
lifting annual sales to their highest level since 1989, Statistics
Canada reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In December, 144,555 new motor vehicles were sold in the
country, up 14.6 percent from November and 32.8 percent from a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
Vehicle dealers "might have drawn some January business into
December by offering their customers strong incentives on the
purchase of new motor vehicles," the statistics agency suggested.
</P>
<P>
This shift in sales, coupled with the ice storm in Quebec and
Eastern Ontario provinces, will cause new motor vehicles sales to
drop drastically in January, 1998, it said.
</P>
<P>
Canada's new motor vehicle sales have been on the rise since
April 1996 following a year of relatively flat sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
