<DOCNO> XIE19980212.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Leonean Ministers Flee to Guinea, Eecomog </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 11 (Xinhua) -- As heavy fighting continues at
the outskirts of the Sierra Leonean capital Freetown, some of the
ministers of the military government have escaped to neighboring
Guinea, the Nigerian defense headquarters said this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Quoting an ECOMOG source in Freetown, Nigeria's Department of
Defense Information said the ministers "disguise as refugees and
join other people who are fleeing for safety".
</P>
<P>
The number of the fleeing ministers was not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Since the fighting broke out between the junta forces and the
west African peacekeeping force known as ECOMOG last Thursday,
about 1,000 people have reportedly fled Freetown to Guinea.
</P>
<P>
The defense headquarters also slammed the propaganda antics by
the junta that the ECOMOG troops are killing innocent civilians.
</P>
<P>
The allegations "are false and without foundation", the
defense headquarters said in a press released signed by Fodwin
Ugbo, Acting Director of Defense Information.
</P>
<P>
"The people's army and the RUF (Revolutionary United Front, a
former rebel group allied to the junta after the May 25 coup last
year) fighting for the junta are without military uniforms. They
wear civil dress and mix with civilians when carrying out their
nefarious activities," it said.
</P>
<P>
Accusing the junta of equally concentrating their arms and
ammunition, especially missiles and anti-aircraft weapons in
civilian areas, the defense headquaters said the ECOMOG troops
have been very conscious to avoid firing on these areas.
</P>
<P>
"The junta have also resorted to looting and molesting
innocent civilians as the ECOMOG troops are closing towards
freetown," it said.
</P>
<P>
"The ECOMOG High Command believes that peaceful negotiation to
restore the legitimate government of President Alhaji Kabbah can
stop these hostilities," it added.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian-led ECOMOG is in Sierra Leone to enforce
sanctions and embargo imposed on the junta by west African
countries and the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the sub-regional force is advancing
towards the center of Freetown after the capture of some
"strategic areas" in the suburbs.
</P>
<P>
The military pressure is seen to aimed at forcing the junta to
follow the peace accord signed between the junta and west African
countries in the Guinean capital of Conakry last October.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, the junta is to quit power on April 22 this
year.
</P>
<P>
The latest intense fighting has forced the close-down of
banks, shops and schools in Freetown and the fleeing of local
residents to neighboring countries, especially Guinea.
</P>
<P>
A United Nations refugee agency spokesman was earlier quoted
as saying that Guinea has become home to some 250,000 Sierra
Leonean refugees, most of who fled after the first coup in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Some 80,000 of them fled after the coup last May, according to
the U.N.High Commissioner for Refugees.  
</P>
</TEXT>
