<HEADLINE> U.S. Stresses Crisis Can Only Be Resolved by Iraq's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The current crisis over
UN weapons inspection in Iraq can only be resolved by Iraq's full
compliance with the relevant resolutions of the Security Council
of the United Nations, U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations Bill
Richardson stressed here today.
</P>
<P>
Richardson was responding to reports that Iraqi Foreign
Minister Mohammed Saeef Al-Sahaf had announced in Cairo Wednesday
Iraq supports a Russian proposal to allow U.N. weapons inspections
of all Iraqi sites in order to avoid a military strike.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, the U.S. Ambassador said," We do not
think there should be any deals or compromises. We feel very
strongly that there should be clear and unfetered access to all
sites by UN inspectors and that the integrity of the United
Nations Special Commission(UNSCOM) should be maintained."
</P>
<P>
"We think the Russian and French proposals are very serious and
well-intentioned. We have reservations about any proposal that
dose not fully comply with UN Council resolutions," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Problem can only be resolved by Iraq's full compliance
with the resolutions of the Security Council," Richardson
stressed.  
</P>
