<HEADLINE> Lebanon Releases New Statistics on Population </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 11 (Xinhua) -- A latest survey on population
released by Lebanon's Central Statistics Board (CSB) Wednesday
shows that the number of people permanently living in Lebanon
stands at 4.006 million, of whom 7.5 percent are non-Lebanese.
</P>
<P>
The survey was released by Secretary General of the CSB
Robel Kasferyou at a news conference.
</P>
<P>
The survey indicates that one third of residents in the
country live in the capital city of Beirut and its suburbs.
</P>
<P>
The number of people under the age of 20 makes up 38.9 percent
of the total population, down from 50 percent in 1970.
</P>
<P>
The workforce in the country stands at 34 percent of the entire
population and the percentage of illiterate people has decreased
from 31.8 percent in 1970 to 11.6 percent in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment rate reaches 8.5-9 percent among males, and
7.2 percent among females, the survey said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
