<HEADLINE> Egypt: Iraq Closer to Implementing UN Resolutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Presidential Advisor
Osama el-Baz said Wednesday that Iraq is edging closer to
implementing the U.N. resolutions, the Middle East News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Iraq was "inching closer to implementing these resolutions,"
Baz said after Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak met with Iraqi
Foreign Minister Mohammad Saeed el-Sahhaf who arrived here
earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
El-Sahhaf told reporters after the meeting that Baghdad has
agreed to open eight presidential sites to international arms
inspectors appointed by United Nations Secretary General Kofi
Annan.
</P>
