<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 11 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Wednesday sent a letter to his Bosnian counterpart Alija
Izetbegovic to explain the visit to France by the president of
Bosnian Serb republic, Biljana Plavsic.
</P>
<P>
Izetbegovic has protested the high-level welcoming ceremony
granted to Plavsic by Chirac on Monday in the Elysee presidential
palace on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said in his letter that he asked Plavsic to help the
return of refugees to their home villages and contribute to the
strengthening of the central government of Bosnia, Agence
France-Presse quoted French diplomats in Sarajevo as saying.
</P>
<P>
The French president described the response of Plavsic as
"positive and encouraging for the future."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman has expressed
astonishment over the protest by Bosnian president over the visit
by Plavsic.
</P>
<P>
"We have learnt with astonishment the communique of the
(Bosnian) presidency which presented in a wrong way the position
of France toward Bosnia and its motive in receiving Madame
Plavsic," said the spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
While calling on Bosnia to "lift" its misunderstanding toward
France, the spokeswoman said that France wishes to reinforce
"relations of friendship and cooperation with the state of
Bosnia-Herzegovina, of which Republika Srspka makes up an
entity."
</P>
<P>
President Chirac gave Plavsic a welcoming ceremony for a head
of state at the Elysee Palace Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for Plavsic to have received such
high-level welcome from a foreign country.
</P>
<P>
Bosnian President Izetbegovic said in a communique that he was
"deeply offended" by the treatment given by France to Plavsic.
</P>
<P>
France said that it received Plavsic in order to support the
forces in favor of peace among Bosnian Serbs and to isolate
ultra-nationalists and war criminals.
</P>
<P>
Paris also wishes to encourage Bosnian Serbs to continue an
opening policy and contribute to the building of a pluralistic and
democratic country in Bosnia. 
