<HEADLINE> Britain Wants UN to Reach Quick Agreement on Iraqi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 11 (Xinhua) -- It was important for
the security Council of the United Nations to adopt a resolution
on the newly proposed oil-for -food plan for Iraq as soon as
possible so as to help the Iraqi people, British Ambassador to the
United Nations Sir John Weston said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, Weston said the original draft had been
amended, presumably to take in some proposals in a rival French
draft, which was now no longer on the table.
</P>
<P>
"It is very important to get one with that resolution. We are
coming in with a slightly amended and consolidated draft
resolution," he told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"We want to get one with that as fast as possible in order to
give the Secretary-General the support he needs for his proposals
and also to bring the help we need to the Iraqi people," he added.
</P>
<P>
The UN chief recommended to increase the amount of the oil Iraq
can sell in every six months from the current 2 billion U.S.
dollars to 5.2 billion dollars. The move is aimed to alleviate the
suffering of the Iraqi People under the UN Sanctions imposed on
Iraq since 1990.  
</P>
</TEXT>
