<HEADLINE> Clinton to Visit Uganda Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
will visit Uganda next month at the invitation of his Ugandan
counterpart Yoweri Museveni, Radio Uganda reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Clinton is scheduled to arrive here on March 23.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents will hold discussions on bilateral
relations and issues concerning the African continent.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first time for a U.S. president to visit
Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The western countries are in recent years paying more
attention to the rich resources and potential markets in Africa,
and have started to make adjustment of their policies toward this
region.
</P>
<P>
Clinton declared last June that "promotion of development of
African economy" should be included in the U.S. foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
Last December, U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright
visited seven African countries including Uganda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
