<HEADLINE> CA Makes Offer to Acquire CSC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 11 (Xinhua)-- U.S. Computer Associates
International, Inc. (CA) Wednesday announced that it had made an
offer to acquire Computer Science Corporation (CSC) in a merger
transaction.
</P>
<P>
The New York's Long Island-based CA has obtained financing
commitments for the approximately nine billion U.S. dollars
transaction. The combined companies would employ over 50,000
professionals and have revenues of approximately 11 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on today's announcement, CA's founder and Chairman
Charles B. Wang stated that the proposed combination of CA and CSC
would create the next-generation, world-class information
technology services provider.
</P>
<P>
The skills that CSC's employees would bring to CA are critical
to the combined company, and CA plans to retain all of CSC's
employees, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
CA is the world leader in mission-critical business software.
The company develops, licenses and supports more than 500
integrated products that include enterprise computing and
information management, application development, manufacturing and
financial applications.
</P>
<P>
CA has over 11,000 people in 160 offices in 43 countries and
had a revenue of 4.5 billion U.S. dollars in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
