<HEADLINE> EU to Donate 2.2 Mln Dlr Aid to Afghan Quake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Britain, the current European
Union (EU) president, announced here today that the EU executive
Commission's Humanitarian Office is to donate about 1.33 million
pounds (about 2.2 million U.S. dollars) for relief in the wake of
Afghanistan's earthquake.
</P>
<P>
British Secretary of State for International Development Clare
Short told the British parliament that the money would be used by
the International Red Cross to provide shelter, medical and water
supplies.
</P>
<P>
Short said, "The remoteness, difficult terrain and poor weather
conditions are making aid deliveries extremely difficult."
</P>
<P>
The British secretary of state noted that Britain had donated
300,000 dollars in response to a United Nations appeal for
assistance last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
