<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese UN Ambassador On Issue of Social Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 11 (Xinhua) -- To guarantee social
stability is the highest priority in social development worldwide,
chinese Ambassador to the United Nations Qin Huasun stressed here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 36th Session of the Commission for Social
Development on promoting social integration, Ambassador Qin said
from a global perspective, many social problems, such as poverty,
unemployment, drug, ethnic conflict and organized crimes, are yet
to be resolved, and humanity is still faced with grave challenges.
</P>
<P>
Qin said these problem, if not solved at an early date, would
lead to social unrest, or even violent conflict.
</P>
<P>
Qin pointed out when social stability is not guaranteed, social
development is only empty words. Therefore, to ensure social
stability is the highest priority in social development.
</P>
<P>
Noting speeding up economic growth is the prerequisite for
promoting social integrity, Qin said all other rights of the
people of developing countries can hardly be realized if, first
and foremost, their right to have enough food and clothing is not
yet realized.
</P>
<P>
The Ambassador said since countries differ in their political,
economic, social and cultural background, governments should
formulate their policies, measures and programs for the promotion
of social integration in light of their own national conditions.
</P>
<P>
He stressed governments should proceed from the practical
conditions, and formulate and implement policies and regulations
to guarantee, in real terms, their people's rights to participate
in social life.
</P>
<P>
Qin said expanding international cooperation and rich countries
helping poorer ones are indispensable conditions for promoting
social integration. He called for settlement through broad
cooperation of, and joint efforts by, the international community.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
