<HEADLINE> Israel Celebrates Jubilee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kiryat Gat (Israel), February 11 (Xinhua) -- Israel kicked off
the celebrations of its jubilee here Wednesday with its leaders'
pledge to bring the country into a bright future.
</P>
<P>
Israeli President Ezer Weizman, Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu and other dignitaries attended the simple inaugurating
ceremony held in this newly-built town, about 80 kilometers
southwest of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
While declaring the opening of the celebrations, Weizman asked
the countrymen not to forget those who have laid down their lives
for the country and join hands to help Israel have peace with all
countries.
</P>
<P>
In a short address, Netanyahu said 50 years have elapsed since
Israel came into being and it is a miracle that Israel has made
great progress in economic development during such a short period.
</P>
<P>
The chance for peace still exists in this region, and Israel
will grasp it to realize peace with all nations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Weizman and Netanyahu planted trees here during the ceremony,
which is part of the plan to plant 500,000 trees in 50 locations
of Israel.
</P>
<P>
The Jewish State was founded on May 14, 1948. 
</P>
</TEXT>
