<HEADLINE> Arrangement for HK Legislative Election Nomination Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The nomination of candidates
for the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region's first
Legislative Council elections this May will begin on April 9
through April 24, it was announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
As for the subsector election on April 2 to form the 800-member
Election Committee, which should be held before the elections for
geographical constituencies, functional constituencies and the
Election Committee, prospective candidates may submit nomination
forms from March 13 to 20.
</P>
<P>
Woo Kwok-hing, chairman of the Electoral Affairs Commission
(EAC), told a press conference here Thursday afternoon that
details are set out in five notices to be gazetted Friday.
</P>
<P>
The elections, slated for May 24, will produce a 60-member
Legislative Council, made up of 20 to be returned from the
geographical constituencies through direct election, 30 by
functional constituencies and 10 by the 800-member Election
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Woo said that completed nomination forms must be handed in to
the relevant Returning Officer or Assistant Returning Officers by
a nominee in person, and in the case of geographical
constituencies, by one of the nominees on a list.
</P>
<P>
Free legal advice would be made available to prospective
candidates from February 16. People intending to contest the
general election on May 24 may apply for legal advice from
February 16 to April 8.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
