Albanian President Rexgeo Mejdani had discussed the issue of
"Eighth Corridor" from the Adriatic coast to Varna Harbour of
Bulgaria during their talks.
</P>
<P>
Meydani arrived in Ankara Wednesday evening for a three-day
official visit to Turkey to boost the existing bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Demirel said that this corridor will serve to link the regional
people in a bid to develop economy.
</P>
<P>
He added that they exchanged views on the promotion of the
bilateral ties and on the regional issues during the talks,
stating: "We protect the development of cooperation and peace
among the Balkan states."
</P>
<P>
In his part, Meydani said that Albania is ready to develop
political dialog between Albania and Turkey, adding that the two
countries should increase mutual high-ranking visits in the
future, aimed at realizing this development.
</P>
<P>
He said that he is satisfied with the defense cooperation
between the two countries, adding that Albania will continue this
cooperation in the framework of "Partnership for Peace."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Meydani met with Chief of the General Staff of
the Turkish Armed Forces Ismail Hakki Karadayi, expressing his
gratitude to Turkey for cooperation in the field of military
defense.
</P>
<P>
He said that Albania is expecting Turkey's aid and
contributions to the founding of a disciplinary Albania army.
</P>
</TEXT>
