<HEADLINE> Tajik President Appoints Opposition Leaders to Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Tajik President Emomali
Rakhmonov appointed several Islamist opposition leaders to his
coalition government, the Interfax news agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Rakhmonov's spokesman Zafar Saidov as saying
that Davlat Usmon, chief of staff of the opposition's armed
forces, was named minister of economy and foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Other opposition members appointed were Davlatbek Makhsudov as
minister of water resources and Khudoberdy Khuliknazarov as labor
and employment minister.
</P>
<P>
And Rakhmim Karimov was to head the Tajik Customs Committee.
</P>
<P>
The appointment was seen as a key step in the settlement of a
four-year civil war in the Central Asian country.
</P>
<P>
The Russian-backed Rakhmonov government signed an inter-Tajik
peace accord with the Islamist opposition last year to end the
civil war.
</P>
<P>
A national reconciliation commission was created later to
supervise the implementation of the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the opposition should hold the posts of
deputy prime minister and control six ministries and seven state
committees in the coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Saidov said Thursday's appointment showed the president's
effort to cooperate with the commission on a timely and complete
implementation of the peace accord. 
</P>
</TEXT>
