<HEADLINE> Sino-Russian Relations to Develop Further: Ambassador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 12 (Xinhua) -- This year should see an all-out
development of the Sino-Russian relations, especially in trade and
economic cooperation, China's top diplomat here said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral relations, said Li Fenglin, Chinese ambassador to
Russia, in an interview given to Itar-Tass News Agency prior to
Chinese Premier Li Peng's visit here, bore great fruits last year.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng is scheduled to arrive next Tuesday for a two-day stay.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Chinese and Russian leaders exchanged a number of
visits, and the two countries finished the survey and demarcation
of the eastern section of their common border, Li Fenglin said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Chinese ambassador said, the two sides
established the Sino-Russian Friendship Committee for Peace and
Development, which was oriented towards the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
These achievements not only pushed forward the Sino-Russian
relations, he said, but also established a model for the
state-to-state relations among other countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
Besides Li Peng's upcoming official visit here, Chinese
President Jiang Zemin will have an informal meeting with Russian
President Boris Yeltsin in the year's second half, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The planned exchanges between Chinese and Russian leaders would
bring new momentum for pushing further ahead the relationship
between the two neighboring countries, the ambassador said.
</P>
