<HEADLINE> American Snowdoarder Killed by Avalanche </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- An American snowboarder
was killed an avalanche at Donner Summit of Truckee, California,
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jamil Khan, 22, was swept away when a cornice of ice and snow
gave way and plunged down the mountain slope.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers found Khan buried beneath 0.9 meters of snow
and flew him by helicopter to a hospital where he was pronounced
dead.
</P>
<P>
Khan competed in the U.S. Olympic Trials and finished second
in a December qualifier. He finished lower in the two January
trials and just missed a spot on the U.S. Olympic snowboard
team. 
