staff of the Netherlands to visit China since the two nations
forged diplomatic ties, and cited the visit as a major event in
the relations between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Contacts between the two armed forces have gradually advanced
with the full restoration of relations, said Fu, adding that Van
Den Breemen's tour will further enhance understanding between the
two armed forces and start a new phase in the friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
Fu addressed the Chinese government's position on
weapons inspections in Iraq by stressing that China advocates a
peaceful settlement of the dispute and firmly opposes the use of
force. He said that China has made positive efforts to ensure
a peaceful settlement of the ongoing crisis.
</P>
<P>
Fu briefed the Netherlands delegation on China's foreign
policy of independence and peace, as well as its national
defence policy and efforts to build the PLA.
</P>
<P>
Van Den Breemen stessed the importance of contacts between the
two sides and emphasised that the Netherlands values the
development of the relations between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Van Den Breemen also briefed his counterpart on the defense
policy and military developments of his country.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of General Staff of the PLA
participated in the disussions.
</P>
<P>
Van Den Breemen arrived here this morning for a visit at
the invitation of Fu. 
