<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Publishes First Standard Chinese Dictionary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- China's first standard Chinese
dictionary has been published by the Language Publishing House in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The dictionary includes 13,000 Chinese characters which
strictly follow the state-set standards on language use.
</P>
<P>
To standardize the Chinese dictionaries, the cultural and
educational departments have established a series of regulations
in recent years, and printing a standard Chinese dictionary was
put into the list of the country's key cultural projects in the
early 1990s.
</P>
<P>
Headed by linguist Lu Shuxiang, more than 20 Chinese experts
and scholars compiled the dictionary in the last six years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
