<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With Pakistan Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin
expressed confidence in the fact that good-neighborly
Sino-Pakistani friendship and reciprocal cooperation will be
carried forward from generation to generation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark this afternoon during a meeting with
visiting Pakistan Prime Minister Mohammad Nawaz Sharif. Jiang
pointed to the fact that the two countries and their people
treasure the traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, or his third meeting with Sharif, Jiang
expressed his belief that the visit will further advance the
development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said that China and Pakistan enjoy close relations and a
time-honored friendship. He added that the Pakistani government
considers the bilateral friendship as a cornerstone of its foreign
policy.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani leader thanked China for its assistance in his
nation's economic development, and expressed the hope that the
current visit will advance bilateral economic and trade
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that the bilateral friendship is deeply rooted in
the hearts of the two peoples, with decades of development
testifying to the consistent pursuit of peace and development
closely linking the two nations.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his appreciation for the Pakistani government's
position on settling relations with its neighbors through peaceful
negotiations, and wished Pakistan further success in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed to profound changes in the international situation
and the general trend towards mitigation and stability. Moreover,
he cited multipolarization as an irresistible historical trend
which witnessed progress both worldwide and regionally.
</P>
<P>
The new international situation involving the mankind's march
towards a new century is a common mission entrusted to developing
countries during modern times. The key centers on whether or not
people throughout the world will seize the opportunity to build a
just and rational international political and economic order.
</P>
</TEXT>
