<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Netanyahu: Israeli Not Count on Iraqi Promise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Commenting on Iraq's pledge
not to attack Israel, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
said Thursday that he does not base decisions on Israeli security
on Iraq's promises.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in Tel Aviv after taking part in the election of
chairman of Likud's Central Committee, Netanyahu said Israel is
taking all necessary precautions for any eventualities.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz said Wednesday that Iraq
had no intention or any plan to attack anybody except the
aggressor.
</P>
<P>
But Netanyahu refused to answer a question about the reported
exchange of messages between Israel and Iraq in the past
days. Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai confirmed Tuesday that
calming messages had been exchanged between Israel and Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The message of not to attack Israel was reportedly conveyed by
Russian Ambassador to Israel Mikhail Bogdanov when he met Monday
with Israeli Knesset (Parliament) Speaker Dan Tichon.
</P>
<P>
Since the possibility of an American-British military strike
against Iraq increases, there have been a panic among Israelis who
fear about possible biological and chemical retaliation by
Iraq. In the 1991 Gulf War, Iraq fired 39 Scud missiles with
conventional warheads at Israel.
</P>
<P>
Despite the repeated assurances issued by political leaders
that an Iraqi attack was highly unlikely, anxious citizens have
been flooding gas masks distribution centers across the
country. Under public pressure, Israeli Army had to seek help from
Israel's foreign missions and foreign countries for urgent supply.
</P>
<P>
This morning, 10 planes loaded with gas masks and other
protection kits landed at the Ben-Gurion Airport from European
countries, which supplied Israel gas masks. Israel has bought or
received as gifts about 400,000 gas masks in recent days
following the shortage of supply to foreign workers in Israel and
Palestinian residents living in areas under Israeli sole
control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
