<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Qiao Shi Meets Public Figures in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator Qiao
Shi  said here Thursday he believed that Hong Kong compatriots
will make concerted efforts under the Special Administrative
Region (SAR) government to build a more prosperous Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC), made these remarks during a meeting with
a dozen public figures in Hong Kong Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
Among them were Ann Tse-kai and leading members of the former
Basic Law drafting and advisory committees and of the former
Preparatory Committee for the HKSAR, members of the HKSAR Basic
Law Committee under the NPC Standing Committee and of the
Presidium of the Conference for Electing HKSAR Deputies to the
Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
Qiao spoke highly of Hong Kong compatriots' contributions to
maintaining HK's prosperity and stability and to HK's smooth
return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the general situation in Hong Kong has been good
with the Basic Law well implemented since the SAR was established
nearly eight months ago. The SAR government under Tung Chee Hwa
has managed local affairs effectively and done a huge amount of
fruitful work. All this has helped maintain Hong Kong's prosperity
and stability.
</P>
<P>
"We are glad to see such a good beginning in the SAR," Qiao
said.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the Hong Kong compatriots will support the SAR
government under the leadership of Tung Chee Hwa more
energetically and make concerted efforts to build a more
prosperous Hong Kong," he added.
</P>
<P>
Present at the meeting were Qiao Shi's wife Yu Wen, Director of
the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch Jiang Enzhu, Deputy
Secretary General of the NPC Standing Committee Liu Zhen, Deputy
Director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State
Council Liu Mingqi and Deputy Secretary General of the NPC
Standing Committee Zhou Chengkui.
</P>
<P>
Thursday morning, Qiao Shi and his wife visited the Extension
of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center where the
handover ceremony was held on June 30 last year.
</P>
<P>
The couple also mounted the 70-storied Bank of China Building
to get a bird's-eye view of Hong Kong. 
</P>
