<HEADLINE> 47 People Killed In Firework Explosions In North China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Forty-seven people were
killed and dozens injured in last month's two explosions of
fireworks in Fengrun and Lincheng counties, in north China's Hebei
Province, according official reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The accidents both occurred on January 24, a few days before
the Spring Festival, the Chinese Lunar New Year's Day which fell
on January 28 this year, when people were flocking in local
markets to buy goods.
</P>
<P>
The two explosions were caused by the same mistake: vendors
tried to show off their goods by igniting some firecrackers in
front of the potential buyers, while ignoring the nearby large
stocks of fireworks.
</P>
<P>
The sparks detonated the firecracker piles and led to
devastating explosions in two cases. Besides the deaths and
injuries, over 20 vehicles were also damaged in the explosions,
according to the reports.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has sent a special team to the two
counties to investigate the cases, and concerned departments have
been asked to step up control over the production, storage,
transportation and sale of fireworks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
