<HEADLINE> HK Grants to Aid Northwestern China Snowstorm Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Disaster Relief
Fund Advisory Committee has approved two grants for emergency
relief for the snowstorm victims in northwestern China's Qinghai
province.
</P>
<P>
One grant of 2.6 million HK dollars (0.33 million U.S. dollars)
was to Oxfam Hong Kong and another of 3.5 million HK dollars (0.44
million U.S. dollars) was to World Vision Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The committee, chaired by Administrative Secretary Anson Chan,
is concerned about the hardship suffered by the victims and hopes
that the two grants could help provide some immediate relief.
</P>
<P>
To ensure that the money will be used for the purpose
designated, the Special Administrative Region (SAR) government has
required the two agencies concerned to submit an evaluation report
and an audited account on the use of the grants.  
</P>
