<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Prices of Construction Materials Drop in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The price index of most
construction materials dropped in the last three months of 1997 in
Macao, latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
Thursday show that the average price index of construction
materials dropped 0.4 percent from the previous three months
period.
</P>
<P>
The price index of steel, lumber, red bricks, porcelain
products, glass, pipes and cement all dropped between 0.2 and 4.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
But the price index of lime, macadam, paint and sanitary
equipment increased between 0.2 and 0.7 percent. The price index
of aluminum, sand and concrete remained the same as in the
previous quarter.
</P>
<P>
The index of paint rose by the largest margin of 0.7 percent
among all construction materials from the previous quarter, while
that of red bricks dropped by the largest margin of 4.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The property market has plunged into the doldrums since
1993. There are about 30,000 empty house units waiting for buyers
in Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
