<HEADLINE> hke021252--Singapore's First Satellite to Be Launched in 3 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's first ever
satellite is in its final stage of production and will be launched
in three months time, Singapore Television reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It said that the 280-million-U.S.-dollar project is being built
in France.
</P>
<P>
The main control station will be located at Seletar in northern
part of the Singapore island, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The satellite will focus on supporting broadcast services,
while telecommunications and data services will make up 20
percent, it said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
