<HEADLINE> "China News Pictorial" Publishes 1997 Selection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A collective edition of major
news events in 1997 has been published here by "China News
Pictorial," a comprehensive news weekly launched by Xinhua News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
The publisher today donated this large-scale collection to the
Central Archives of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
Party Literature Research Center of the CPC Central Committee for
storage.
</P>
<P>
The 100-page collection with a theme of "Unforgettable 1997"
contains news report on such major political, economic and
cultural events in the past year as the death of Deng Xiaoping,
the return of Hong Kong to the motherland, the 15th CPC National
Congress, the damming of the Yangtze River at Three Gorges and the
Yellow River at Xiaolangdi, and President Jiang Zemin's U.S. visit.
</P>
<P>
All the pictures and articles, which were selected from those
released by Xinhua to China and overseas, are regarded as
historical and authoritative.  
</P>
</TEXT>
