<HEADLINE> Fund in Zhejiang Helps Young Scientists Conduct Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 12 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang
Province has set up a special fund to help its young scientists
conduct scientific research.
</P>
<P>
A special fund, which was set up two years ago, has so far
raised more than 4 million yuan to help 21 young scientists in the
fields of mathematics, chemistry, biology, geology, information
technology, materials and engineering.
</P>
<P>
The fund was sponsored by the provincial foundation of natural
science, which was established 10 years ago.
</P>
<P>
During those 10 years, the foundation has offered abundant
financial help to nearly 10,000 scientists and technicians in the
province. One-third of them are 35 or under.  
</P>
