<HEADLINE> Turkish President Lauds Ties With Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel said here Thursday that the good ties and cooperation
between the governments of Turkey and Albania will set an example
for the whole region.
</P>
<P>
Demirel made the remark at the welcoming ceremony in the
presidential palace for Albanian President Rexhep Mejdani, who
arrived here Wednesday evening for a three-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
"There exists no problem between Turkey and Albania," said
Demirel, adding that Albania is an important partner of Turkey in
various European forums, southeastern European cooperation and the
Black Sea economic cooperation process, which serve peace and
stability in this region.
</P>
<P>
"We want our partner to develop in a bid to contribute to
peace and prosperity in the region of southeastern Europe," he
said.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Mejdani said he appreciates Turkey's aid to
Albania, saying the bright relations between Albania and Turkey
will continue.
</P>
<P>
He said that his visit is a great opportunity for the
cooperation between the two peoples, and "will play an important
role in our right partnership way to Europe."
</P>
<P>
Following the ceremony, the two presidents started talks on the
development of bilateral ties as well as a number of regional and
international issues. 
</P>
