<HEADLINE> Reception Marks Sino-Uruguayan Establishment of Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) held a
reception here today to mark the 10th anniversary of establishment
of diplomatic relations between China and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reception, CPAFFC President Qi Huaiyuan said
China and Uruguay share a long history of friendship, and that
since the forging of bilateral diplomatic ties, the two countries
have seen a stable and smooth development in bilaterial relations.
</P>
<P>
Exchanges of high-level visits between the two countries have
been frequent, and cooperation in the fields of economy, culture
and education has been successful, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The president expressed appreciation for Uruguay's one-China
stand and its support to China in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said he is confident in the further development of
Sino-Uruguayan friendly cooperative relations through joint
efforts by the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Uruguayan ambassador to China Alvaro Alvarez said the two
countries have made great achievements in the development of the
Sino-Uruguayan relations over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
The two countries share same ideas in major international
issues, the ambassador said, adding that bilateral friendly
cooperation in the political, economic, trade and cultural areas
have been expanded greatly.
</P>
<P>
China has been Uruguay's third largest trading partner
in the world, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador expressed his hope that the Sino-Uruguayan
friendly cooperation will be further strengthened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
