<HEADLINE> Agassi Beats Kuerten Easily in Sybase Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Former world number one
Andre Agassi of the United States showed his strong comeback by
trouncing French Open champion Gustavo Kuereten of Brazil 6-3, 6-1
in the second round of the 340,000 U.S. dollars Sybase Open in San
Jose, California, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Agassi needed only 41 minutes to thrash the
number 12-ranked Kuerten from every corner of the court.
</P>
<P>
The victory was Agassi's first time over a player ranked within
the top 15 since last August.
</P>
<P>
"It was the best tennis I've played this year," Three grand
slams titlist Agassi said.
</P>
<P>
"I couldn't find anyway to change the match," Kuerten said.
"He was playing fast and hard and close to the lines. He's been
one of the best players in the world, and I'm just the new guy
around here. I have a lot to do before I get to that level."
</P>
<P>
In other second round matches, second seed Michael Chang of the
United States edged George Bastl of Switzerland 7-5, 6-3, and
Jordi Burillo of Spain romped Andrea Gaudenzi of Italy 6-3, 6-1.
</P>
