<HEADLINE> HK Trade Official to Attend APEC Meeting in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Director-general
of Trade Alan Lai will lead the Hong Kong, China delegation to
attend the First Senior Official Meeting (SOM I) in 1998 of the
Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) to be held on February
16-17 in Malaysia, the Trade Department said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation comprises officials from the Trade and Industry
Bureau, the Economic Services Bureau, the Home Affairs Bureau and
several departments concerned.
</P>
<P>
Preceding SOM I, senior officials will gather for a retreat on
February 14 and 15 for an informal exchange of ideas and
priorities of themes for the APEC this year.
</P>
<P>
At SOM I, senior officials will consider how to take forward
instructions from APEC Economic Leaders and Ministers set out at
their meetings held in Vancouver, Canada in November 1997.
</P>
<P>
Early voluntary sectoral liberalization and other trade and
investment liberalization and facilitation issues, public-private
sector partnership in infrastructure development, and APEC agenda
on science and technology industry cooperation are among major
issues to be discussed.
</P>
<P>
This is the first SOM under the Malaysian APEC chairmanship.
The second and third SOMs will be held in June and September
respectively. The APEC Ministerial and Economic Leaders Meetings
will be held in Kuala Lumpur in November 1998.  
</P>
