<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 people were
killed and 76 others injured in separate road accidents during
last 24 hours in Rajasthan state in southwest India, the Press
Trust of India (PTI) said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Police said six people including an infant and two women were
killed and four others injured when a jeep and a bus collided
head-on on Delhi-Mumbai national highway between Dholpur and Agra
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In another mishap, four people were killed and 14 others
injured when a mini bus and trolley collided at Ghasipura under
Manoharpur police station on Jaipur-Delhi highway.
</P>
<P>
Four people including two women and a child were killed and 15
others injured in a collision between a jeep and a truck near
Devri on Chittoreg Arh and Udaipur state highway.
</P>
<P>
A Janata Dal (JD) worker was killed and 43 others injured, five
of them seriously, when the truck in which they were traveling
overturned on a bridge near Banswara Wednesday evening, police
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
All the injured were admitted to a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
The JD workers were going from Danapur to Banswara for
electioneering.  
