<HEADLINE> Government Lots Sold for 100 Million HK Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The public auction of two
residential sites Thursday put more than 100 million HK dollars
(12.8 million US dollars) into the Special Administrative Region
(SAR) government's coffers.
</P>
<P>
The two government lots, both in the "New Territories", drew
active bidding from property developers and were finally sold for
a total of 101.6 million HK dollars (13 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The first site, with an area of 4,133 square meters, was bought
by the Light Corporation Limited for 90 million HK dollars (11.5
million US dollars), more than doubling the opening bid of 38
million HK dollars (4.8 million US dollars). It is designated for
private residential purposes.
</P>
<P>
The second lot, with an area of 88.2 square meters, was sold to
New Foundation Development Limited for 11.6 million HK dollars
(1.5 million US dollars). It can be transformed into a multi-story
residential and commercial block.
</P>
<P>
The buyers said that they thought prices for the two lots were
reasonable.  
