<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks End Down As Unemployment Figures Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket
closed weaker Thursday on the back of profit-taking among the
resource majors and a lack of positive domestic news after the
release of January employment figures failed to inspire investors.
</P>
<P>
The official data showed the unemployment rate rose to 8.2 in
January from 8.1 in December, and the number of jobless was rose
by 3000 to 756,100.
</P>
