<HEADLINE> Southwest Chinese Railway Safety During Festival Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The railways of southwestern
China had carried 6.1 million passengers as of yesterday during
the Spring Festival peak period, according to the Chengdu Railway
Administration, which is in charge of the area.
</P>
<P>
Since Sichuan Province, where Chengdu is located, and Chongqing
Municipality are home to about 5.5 million transient rural
laborers, railways are incredibly busy during the Spring Festival
holiday, when the majority of them try to go home for festival
celebrations with their relatives.
</P>
<P>
The busy time this year began on January 30, the third day of
the festival, when the daily passenger load exceeded
250,000. Above 60 percent of the trains were overloaded, and there
were another 50,000 to 70,000 passengers waiting to buy tickets at
railway stations.
</P>
<P>
In order to cope with the situation, the Chengdu authorities
introduced 37 temporary trains and sent over 3,000 office workers
to work as train attendants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
