<HEADLINE> Macao Establishes Less New Companies in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The number of new companies
established in Macao last year dropped 11.1 percent compared with
the previous year as a result of economic slowdown, latest
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
on Thursday show that a total of 665 new companies were
established in 1997, with a registered capital of 137.7 million
patacas (17.2 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Compared with the previous year, the number of new firms
dropped 11.1 percent and the registered capital plummeted by 40.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
Most of the new entities deal with wholesale and retail sales,
restaurants and hotels. About 20 percent are engaged in
construction and civil engineering, and about 15 percent are
running finance, insurance, banking, real estate and other service
companies.
</P>
<P>
Only 116 new companies were founded in the last three months of
1997, with a total registered capital of 17.7 million patacas
(2.21 million dollars). Meanwhile nine companies wound up their
business in the period.
</P>
<P>
Macao has seen an economic slowdown since 1993. The economic
growth rate for 1997 was estimated at less than 1 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
