<HEADLINE> Shanghai Official on Pudong Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The mayor of east China's
Shanghai municipality, Xu Kuangdi, told the first session of the
11th Municipal People's Congress today that the Pudong New Area
should open wider to the outside world and use foreign investment
in a more efficient way.
</P>
<P>
Xu said that the area should get more financial organizations,
headquarters of large firms, and markets for production to move to
the area. Foreign banks doing Renminbi business and Sino-overseas
cooperative foreign trade firms will be further encouraged as
well, he added.
</P>
<P>
Export-oriented processing and cargo transport in the
Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone will be expanded, and construction work on
other new industrial bases like the Lujiazui finance trade zone
and the Jinqiao export processing zone, will speed up.
</P>
<P>
The new area has taken shape after five years of construction
work, he noted, and its GDP has increased 23.8 percent annually for
the past five years.
</P>
<P>
It has approved 4,900 foreign-funded projects, with a total
investment of 23.8 billion US dollars. 
