<HEADLINE> 500 Iraqi POW's to Arrive in Baghdad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, February 12 (Xinhua) -- 500 Iraqi prisoners of war
(POWs) detained in Iran will arrive in Baghdad by road within a
few days, Iraqi newspaper "Al-Zaoraa", organ of Iraq's
Journalists Union, said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The paper added that the National Association for the Prisoners
of War Affairs, formed by the Iraqi National Assembly
(parliament), is now getting prepared to welcome the new batch of
POWs.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian authorities are expected to set free more Iraqi
POWs following the successful talks recently with Iraqi Foreign
Minister Mohammed Saeed Al-Sahhaf in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The two countries fought a bloody war between 1980-88. The
issue of POWs is a main obstacle to the normalization of relations
between the two countries. Iraq claimed that about 18,000 Iraqi
POWs are detained in Iran and called on Iran to set free all of
them. 
