<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The European Union will spend
six billion Shillings on the reconstruction of Nairobi-Mombasa
and the Nairobi-Nakuru roads, both key to the road transport
between coastal Kenya to inland and other Great Lakes countries.
</P>
<P>
After the current emergency work on the strategic roads is
over, tendering for the major work will start mid this year and
the actual work at the beginning of next year.
</P>
<P>
The EU will also finance a feasibility study on the section of
the Great North Road to Uganda to be financed by various donors,
the Daily Nation reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
EU head of delegation Lutz Sulzmann said that, however, the
Kenyan government would be expected to meet certain standards of
road maintenance first.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan government must enforce the law on weight capacity
as overloaded vehicles damage the roads before their projected
life span, he said after signing an agreement for the financing
with Minister of Public Works Kikalya Kones.
</P>
<P>
Money collected from motorists as road maintenance levy must
be managed by the ministry of public works to ensure
transparency, he added.
</P>
<P>
Another 750 million Shilling project under the funding of EU
would commence next Wednesday for Eastern province, he revealed.
</P>
