<HEADLINE> Canadian Snowboarding Champion Disqualified from Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, Japan, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Court of Arbitration for
Sport has overturned a decision by the International Olympic Committee
to strip Canadian snowboarder Ross Rebagliati of his gold medal,
Canadianteam press chief Sylie Bigras said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Rebagliati, gold medalist of the men's giant slalom, was
disqualified from the Winter Olympics on Wednesday after testing
positive for marijuana.
</P>
<P>
IOC Director-General Francois Carrard said on Wednesday that
metabolized marijuana was detected in an "A" sample, and then a "B"
sample confirmed 17.8 nanograms per milliliter of the substance.
</P>
<P>
The IOC has no minimum amounts set for substance infractions, but
the International Ski Federation to which Rebagliati is a member sets
15 nanogram limit.
</P>
<P>
Deciding between issuing a warning or sanctions to the snowboarder,
both the medical commission and the IOC Executive Board voted in
favour of sanctions.
</P>
<P>
The medical commission voted 13-12 to recommend sanctioning the
snowboarder to the IOC which takes the action. The IOC executive
board voted 3-2 with 2 abstentions on the matter, Carrard said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980212.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High-Tech Methods Aid China's Military Mapping Units </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Mapping units under the
Chinese Army have been adopting high-tech means during the last
several years, an officer with the Headquarters of General Staff
of the People's Liberation Army said today.
</P>
<P>
With the application of modern methods such as satellite
positioning, remote sensing, digital survey and drawing and an
advanced geographical information system, the units are able to
carry out dynamic and diverse mapping, he said.
</P>
<P>
Providing detailed topographical data, the mapping units have
significantly improved the smooth progress of military drills. Now
the mapping units are playing a vital role in raising the Army's
combat effectiveness.
</P>
<P>
Simulated action systems have been developed on the basis of
digital maps and satellite positioning enables troops to fulfill
all-weather tasks in various terrain, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
