<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of Malnourished Children Drops in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has improved The
nutritional status of children over the past decades, with the
percentage of malnourished children dropping from 71.5 percent in
1985 to 59.7 percent in 1995.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed in a survey report entitled The Child
Nutrition Survey of Bangladesh 1995-96 which was released here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The survey was conducted by the Bangladesh Bureau of Statistics
with the financial help of the United Nations Children's Fund.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey report, of the malnourished children
aged six months to six years, about 43 percent were stunted
(chronically undernourished), about 8 percent were wasted
(deficient in weight for height) and another 8 percent were
concurrently stunted and wasted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
