<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Info Tech Firms Capture Bulk of U.S. Venture Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Venture capital firms in
the United States invested 11.4 billion dollars in 1,848
U.S. companies last year, according to a San Francisco-based
research firm.
</P>
<P>
Of the biggest beneficiaries, Silicon Valley absorbed a record
3.6 billion dollars of pension fund and other institutional money,
and in the San Francisco Bay area 592 firms received 3.8 billion
dollars, up 37 percent over 1996. The two areas captured 65
percent of the national total.
</P>
<P>
Nationwide, reported VentureOne, a leading provider of
information and analysis on the venture capital industry, the
picture was similar last year although the growth rate of 16
percent is less than what it was in Silicon Valley and the Bay
area.
</P>
<P>
Investments on communications, Internet and other information
technology companies accounted for 62 percent of the national
total venture money, said VentureOne, adding that the sector
accounted for all the growth in U.S. venture investments. These
totaled 7 billion dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Information technology firms in the Bay area absorbed as many
as 78 percent of local venture investments in the past year. In
1996, IT firms also captured the dominant share of the venture
investment dollars, accounting for 60 percent. It took 47 percent
of the venture money in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
