<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Province Developing Export-oriented Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 12 (Xinhua) -- China's Guangdong Province
will make an effort to increase export-oriented agriculture by
using overseas funds, technology, market information, and
management expertise.
</P>
<P>
This information comes from Ou Guangyuan, the province's
vice-governor, who told a provincial rural work conference that
the government will hold a second investment promotion fair in
Hong Kong in the latter half of the year to attract overseas
investors to agricultural projects.
</P>
<P>
He says that Guangdong has some very distinct advantages for
export-oriented agriculture because of its subtropical resources,
proximity to Hong Kong and Macao, and the vast inland market.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 1,527 overseas-funded enterprises in the
agriculture sector. It also has 489 export bases that use some 600
million US dollars annually and have exports valued at 12 billion
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The boom in export-oriented agriculture has meant changes in
the province's mode of production and the development of more
modern agriculture, Ou says. One foreign-funded food products
factory in the city of Zhuhai, for example, established a
production base on 667 hectares of ground that was able to employ
thousands of farmers for help in growing fruits and vegetables.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
