<DOCNO> XIE19980212.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ambassador on Sino-Yemeni Relations and Middle East Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The upcoming China visit by
President Ali Abdulla Saleh of the Republic of Yemen should
further strengthen the friendly relations and cooperation between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
This view was expressed by Yemen's ambassador to China,
Mohammed Hadi Awad, in an exclusive interview with Xinhua here
today.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the visit, scheduled to begin this weekend, is
to strengthen political ties as well as economic and trade
cooperation between Yemen and China, thus helping promote the
economic development of Yemen and improve the living conditions of
the Yemeni people, the ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
In history, Awad said, Yemen was a transit stop for exported
goods from China to Europe and a link between the East and the
West.
</P>
<P>
China once gave support to Yemen in its struggle against
British colonial rule and for national independence, while Yemen
is among the Arab nations that recognized the People's Republic of
China quickly, Awad said.
</P>
<P>
Starting in the 1950s, Awad said, cooperation between Yemen and
China has been growing and has expanded into trade, science,
technology, culture and other areas.
</P>
<P>
Chinese companies are now doing business in petroleum and
highway construction in Yemen and Chinese doctors are working in
some hospitals in Yemen. The Yemeni government has formulated
plans to encourage private and state-owned firms to cooperate with
Chinese businesses, the ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
At present, he added, more than 120 Yemeni students are
studying in China. Some Chinese schools have offered to help Yemen
with professional training.
</P>
<P>
Extending congratulations to China for the return of Hong Kong
and the scheduled return of Macao, Awad said Yemen hopes that
Taiwan will reunify with its motherland at an early date.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the theories and philosophy of Deng Xiaoping,
through opening to the outside world and the initiative of 'one
country, two systems,' have born fruitful results in both economic
and political aspects," Awad said.
</P>
<P>
Yemen appreciates China's position to support the cause of the
Arabs and to safeguard the people's rights of seeking
independence, stability and development, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the Yemeni government's position on the Middle East peace
process, Awad said it is only when the occupied Palestinian and
Arab territories are returned that Middle East peace can be
realized.
</P>
<P>
The resolutions of the United Nations and the U.N. Security
Council on the Middle East should be implemented, and the
Palestinian people should regain their rights and build their
independent country on their own land, the ambassador said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
