<HEADLINE> Mongolia Exports Oil to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia exported 350
barrels of crude oil to China Wednesday, thus turning a new
page on its oil exportation.
</P>
<P>
A grand ceremony was held at the Tamsag oil field, located in
Dornod Aimak. Mongolian Prime Minister Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan
attended the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The oil was transported to China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region by trucks. Reports said that 360 barrels of oil produced
from the field will be exported every day to China later on.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia has an estimated oil reserves of more than 6 billion
barrels, about half of which are deposited in the thirteen big oil
basins in the western, eastern and southern areas bordering on
China.
</P>
<P>
Oil companies from the United States and Canada are exploring
oil in the east. 
</P>
</TEXT>
