<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Back Home from Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
returned Wednesday from a three-day visit to Italy.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, a number of agreements were signed between
the two countries. The overall economic effect from the visit can
reach 3 billion U.S. dollars, First Deputy Prime Minister Boris
Nembsov was quoted as saying by Interfax News agency.
</P>
<P>
The deals include an agreement between Italy's Fiat and
Russia's Gorky automobile Factory (GAZ) to establish a joint
venture in Russia which can produce 150,000 cars annually, the
news agency said.
</P>
<P>
During Yeltsin's visit in Rome, the Russian and Italian foreign
ministers signed a memorandum of understanding on technical
cooperation and a cooperation accord on cultural affairs and
education.
</P>
<P>
They also issued a joint statement on the Iraqi situation,
appealing for a diplomatic solution to the crisis. 
