<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Stimulates Small Enterprises In Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Investment by multinationals
has stimulated the growth of small and medium-sized enterprises in
the Chinese port city of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Over 200 local firms have produced 300 types of products worth
7.5 billion yuan (903.6 million US dollars) for projects funded by
multinationals.
</P>
<P>
This has helped improve the management and product quality of
these firms, one city official says.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin is the largest port in northern China and has attracted
about 200 multinationals, 13 of which are among the world's top 30
and 6 of which are among the ten most successful companies in the
United States. 
</P>
