<DOCNO> XIE19980212.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Build First Butyl Rubber Production Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese petrochemical group
in March will begin to build the country's first butyl rubber
production equipment, which is able to turn out 30,000 tons of the
special rubber.
</P>
<P>
To date, Yanshan Petrochemical Group has completed
infrastructure preparation for the project including clearance of
the construction site and laying underground pipe lines.
</P>
<P>
As one of the key construction components of the Ninth
Five-Year Plan Period (1996-2000) designed by Sinopec, the project
should facilitate the development of China's auto industry.
</P>
<P>
Butyl rubber is an important material in manufacturing the
innertube of car tires, pharmaceutical products, and electric and
cable lines because of its airtight capacity.
</P>
<P>
The synthesization of the rubber is extremely demanding in
regard to pressure and temperature controls. The technology is now
controlled by a few countries.
</P>
<P>
The butyl rubber project is based on an agreement signed by
Sinopec and Italy's PI Corp. in 1996. According to the agreement,
the Chinese expect to import key parts of the equipment such as
generators from Italy, and bring in PI's expertise in butyl rubber
production.
</P>
<P>
The project is scheduled to start operations in November of
1999.
</P>
<P>
The current global production capacity of butyl rubber is
770,000 tons annually. China's yearly imports total 15,000 tons,
which is valued at 315 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict China's demand for butyl rubber in 2000 will
reach 60,000 tons as a result of the growth of auto
industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
