<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number Of Foreign Trade Enterprises In China Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Official statistics show more
than 160,000 enterprises in China are involved in foreign trade
now.
</P>
<P>
For a long time foreign trade was the sole privilege of certain
state-owned companies, until the reforms and opening up gave a
large number of manufacturers the freedom to handle foreign trade
themselves.
</P>
<P>
By now, there are more than 7,800 industrial enterprises with
foreign trade rights and 295 scientific research institutions are
given such rights.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, these industrial enterprises and research institutions
with foreign trade rights exported 17.56 billion US dollars worth
of goods, up 33.2 percent from 1996, and accounting for 9.6
percent of China's total exports.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show the number of foreign-funded enterprises
reach over 300,000 enterprises in China, and 145,000 of these
already operational. These enterprises did 152.6 billion US
dollars worth of exports and imports, making up 46.9 percent of
the country's total.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
