<HEADLINE> Turkish President to Visit France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel is to pay an official visit to France on February 19 and
20 in a bid to further bilateral relations, local newspaper Daily
News said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Demirel will hold talks with his French counterpart Jacques
Chirac, Prime Minister Lionel Jospin and several ministers during
the visit, the first by a Turkish head of state to Paris in the
past 30 years.
</P>
<P>
The current U.S.-Iraqi stand-off in the Gulf region, relations
between Turkey and the European Union (EU) and Turco-French
cooperation are expected to be taken up during the talks.
</P>
<P>
The French leadership might suggest once again that Turkey
participate in the EU conference which is scheduled to be held in
London next month, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Angered by the EU rejection last December to include it in the
expansion process, Turkey has announced a halt of political
dialogue with organization and turned down an invitation to the
London meeting.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Turkey and France are expected to sign a
goodwill accord aimed at further enhancing the two countries'
cooperation. 
</P>
