<HEADLINE> Sino-Pakistani Economic, Trade Cooperation Emphasized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu
Rongji stressed economic and trade cooperation between China and
Pakistan here this morning when meeting with visiting Pakistani
Prime Minister Mohammad Nawaz Sharif.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the Chinese government attaches importance to
strengthening economic and trade cooperation between the two
countries to inject more vigor into friendly bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government will continue to adopt active measures
to encourage powerful and reputable enterprises and companies to
conduct economic and trade exchanges and economic cooperation with
their Pakistani counterparts, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said he also hopes that Pakistan can provide more products
suited to Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Zhu referred to Sharif as an old friend of
the Chinese people, and voiced his pleasure at meeting him.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that the most noticeable characteristic of
Sino-Pakistani relations is mutual reliance and understanding.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Pakistan is a friendly neighbor, Zhu pointed to
China's satisfaction with the overall development of bilateral
relations since the two countries set up diplomatic ties 47 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
Zhu voiced his conviction that Sharif's current visit to China
would advance to a new stage the overall bilateral partnership
oriented to the next century.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said that he feels like he is returning home every time
he visits China, adding that Pakistan treasures the friendship
between the two governments and people.
</P>
<P>
He said China is the most reliable and trustworthy friend of
Pakistan. China is the hope of developing countries, he said,
adding his congratulations on its economic achievements.
</P>
<P>
He said the Pakistani government will continue to cooperate
with China in international arenas such as the United Nations, and
it will continue to support China's principled stand on issues
such as human rights.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also briefed Sharif on China's economic situation and the
adjustment of its economic structure, especially the concept and
progress of the reform of China's state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He also stated his appreciation for Pakistan's policies and new
measures aimed at developing the economy, attracting foreign
investment and improving Pakistani's lives.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also expressed his thanks for Sharif's invitation to him to
visit Pakistan at his convenience.  
</P>
