<HEADLINE> China Moves to Medal Round at Women's Ice Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, Japan, February 12 (Xinhua) -- China roared back from one
goal down to beat Sweden 3-1 in a women's ice hockey match at the 18th
Olympic Winter Games at the Aqua Wing here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The win secured China a berth in the medal round next week.
</P>
<P>
After finishing the first period which witnessed no goals from both
sides, Sweden broke the deadlock midway through the second period when
Therese Sjoelander fired the puck into an open net from the blue line.
</P>
<P>
Chinese goalie Guo Hong appeared slightly hurt during the melee
before the goal was scored, forcing play to be stopped for about 5
minutes.
</P>
<P>
China dominated the third period, with goals just over a minute
apart by Zhang Lan and Liu Hongmei. Yang Xiuqing dropped in an
insurance goal for China at 18:18 to seal the victory.
</P>
<P>
Chinese team headcoach Zhang Zhinan was quite satisfied with the
results. "I was satisfied with the performance of our team today,
especially since they came from one goal behind to score three times
against Sweden. Their performance was very clear-cut and powerful."
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
