<HEADLINE> China to Carry out National Inventory of Urban Enterprises' Assets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A nationwide inventory and
check of assets of collectively-owned enterprises in urban areas
will be conducted in accordance with the reform process in this
sector, according to sources from the Ministry of Finance.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the ministry, along with the State Economic
and Trade Commission and the State Administration of Taxation, has
jointly issued a circular on implementing this initiative.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for China to organize a unitary
inventory of assets of urban collectively-owned enterprises. The
goals of the inventory are a thorough check and re-evaluation of
the assets in this sector, clarifying ownership, and creating
conditions for the enterprises to adapt to the management
mechanism of a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
The circular said the inventory would be jointly carried out by
the above-mentioned three departments under the unified leadership
of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
All districts and departments throughout the country have been
told to clarify the assets and discover problems through the
inventory, and to reinforce fundamental management to solve
enterprises' weak points so that enterprises can be promoted with
their establishment of modern enterprise and management
mechanisms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
