<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Looking For Tourism Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The city of Shenzhen,
nextdoor to Hong Kong on the north, expects to have 2.4 million
overseas tourists this year, an increase of 3.5 percent over last
year, according to Chi Xiongbiao, deputy director of the city's
Tourism Development Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The city can earn 967 million US dollars from those overseas
tourists, an annual rise of four percent, Chi says.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Shenzhen had eight million domestic and
international tourists and earned 15.67 billion yuan and 930
million US dollars respectively, from them. It has become China's
fourth largest tourist city, after Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Chi says the city's robust tourism growth is because of its
role as a lab for the country's reforms and opening to the outside
world.
</P>
<P>
He says that the city will add the stock market, industrial
exhibition hall, and some high-tech companies to the list of
its tourist sites, along with some shopping malls. 
</P>
