<HEADLINE> Myanmar People Urged to Work For National Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Senior-General
Than Shwe Thursday urged all the nationalities in the country to
participate in the political, economic and social spheres to
achieve the goal of a peaceful, modern and developed new nation.
</P>
<P>
In a message on the occasion of the 51st anniversary of the
Myanmar Union Day, Than Shwe, chairman of the Myanmar State Peace
and Development Council, said "all the national races of the union
have to firmly build a peaceful, modern and developed new nation."
</P>
<P>
He called on the nationalities to cooperate in unity and
magnanimity at the National Convention to work for an enduring new
state constitution.
</P>
<P>
"The new state constitution can raise opportunities to a higher
level and constantly provide political, economic and social
opportunities in building a peaceful, modern and developed new
nation, the national objective," he said.  
