<HEADLINE> Jobless Thais May Receive Loan From Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Jobless people in Thailand
would receive aid from Japan which is considering providing them a
yen loan, the Thai Foreign Ministry said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry, discussions are at the initial
stage, while the amount of the loan will be roughly the same as
that Japan extended to Indonesia, which totaled 200 million yen
(1.6 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Japan is reported to be considering another 500 million yen (4
million dollars) to Indonesia to help relieve the plight of the
unemployed there.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese loan is seen as part of the Japanese government's
efforts to strengthen its regional role in political, economic and
security affairs.
</P>
<P>
But Thai Foreign Minsiter Surin Pitsuwan said he would like
Japan to treat Thailand as a partner rather than an aid recipient.
</P>
