<HEADLINE> Presidential Election to Promote Unity: Armenian Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The current presidential
campaign should promote national unity rather than deepen the
political crisis, Armenia's acting President Robert Kocharyan
noted Wednesday, according to the Interfax Agency.
</P>
<P>
Meeting representatives from the Black Sea Economic Cooperation
Organization (BSECO), Kocharyan added the presidential election
next month will be held in a "fair and understanding" atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
Kocharyan, also the prime minister, said Armenia's financial
market was not affected by the resignation of the president, adding
Armenia implemented all the investment plans with no capital
run-offs, he added.
</P>
<P>
Kocharyan became acting president after the National
Assembly of the Republic of Armenia accepted Ter-Petrosyan's
resignation on February 4.
</P>
<P>
Ter-Petrosyan, president since the country gained
independence after the former Soviet Union disintegrated in 1991,
decided to step down because of a public debate with Kocharyan
over policy toward the controversial Nagorno-Karabakh issue.
</P>
<P>
The presidential election is scheduled to be held on March 16.
</P>
</TEXT>
