<P>
NEW YORK -- The Chinese Constitution provides religious freedom
to citizens and some Westerners accusing China of "religious
persecution" do not understand the reality in China, a
high-ranking official said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
There are over 100 million religious believers in China, and
the church there has printed over 20 million copies of Bible for
them, said Ye Xiaowen, visiting Director of the Religious Affairs
Bureau under the State Council of China.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference that he knew from a friend that at a
recent Washington D.C. seminar on "Religious Persecution in
China", nor speakers or participants were aware of the
figures. (China-Religious Freedom)
