<HEADLINE> Four Poisoned Swans Saved in East China Zoo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Jinan Zoo has successfully
saved the lives of four poisoned swans recently in this capital of
east China's Shandong province.
</P>
<P>
The four swans are now able to eat.
</P>
<P>
However, the zoo failed to bring back a fifth swan.
</P>
<P>
The five swans were discovered by workers of a refinery in
the Shengli Oilfield. They were soon transferred to the Jinan Zoo,
where they received treatment from zoologists and zoo keepers.
</P>
<P>
The unfortunate swans got sick after eating poisoned baits in a
wheat field, which had been meant for troublesome voles and hares.
</P>
<P>
After the incident, the provincial wild animal protection
authorities have taken measures to monitor the local wildlife and
prevent similar incidents.  
</P>
</TEXT>
