<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Government Urged to Clear Arrears </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, February 11 (Xinhua) -- In a resolution adopted on
Wednesday, the Ukrainian parliament urged the government to clear
all the arrears of salaries and pensions totalling more than five
billion gryvnas (about 263 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The parliament demanded that the government work out a time
schedule on the payment and report to it by May 1.
</P>
<P>
It also suggested that officials responsible for the arrears
should be held prosecutable.
</P>
<P>
Answering to the parliament on Wednesday, Finance Minister Igor
Michukov said the government planned to earmark 1.3 billion gryvnas
(about 68.4 million dollars) in this year's budget for clearing
the arrears created by a government's abstinence policy in the past
few years.
</P>
<P>
In order to get loans from the World Bank and the International
Monetary Fund, the Ukrainian government imposed a strict control over the
issuance of bank notes and budget deficit, thus leading to a severe
shortage in funds for salary and pension payment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
