<HEADLINE> Technology Museum to Show Beijing More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- People in Beijing who are
interested in science can expect more things to see in the China
Science and Technology Museum in the next two years, today's
"China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of the museum's construction will start at the
end of this month, and the project is going to be completed before
October 1 of next year, said Liu Jidong, deputy director of the
museum.
</P>
<P>
As the largest one in China, it will open to the to the public
early in 2000.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 100 million yuan (12 million US
dollars), the project has been listed as one of Beijing's key
projects.
</P>
<P>
The present museum, which was completed and opened to the public
in 1988, covers an area of 20,000 square meters, but the space of
the three-storey exhibition hall is only 3,900 sq meters. About
300 ancient and modern items ware on display.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the museum received more than 700,000 people.
</P>
<P>
After the project is finished, Liu said, visitors are expected
to see 500 more items on display regarding the environment,
information technology, life sciences, energy and
communications. Some technological advances will also be displayed
at the hall.
</P>
<P>
Visitors can operate some facilities and do experiments by
themselves, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
