<HEADLINE> "Do It Right for Thailand" Campaign to be Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government is
embarking on a "do it right for Thailand" campaign, an offshoot of
the "Thai-help-Thai" project, according to a local press report
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the campaign is to "show love and patriotism for the
country in this time of economic crisis," the report said.
</P>
<P>
Valentine's Day has been chosen by the government for launching
the campaign aimed at encouraging people to conserve energy and
refrain from buying foreign-made products.
</P>
<P>
Akrapol Sornsuchart, the government spokesman and chairman of
the campaign sub-committee, was quoted as saying that it would in
close collaboration with the Thai-help-Thai campaign to "raise
public awareness of the importance of nationwide austerity."
</P>
<P>
Akrapol said people would be made to realize the adversity of
the economic crisis compounded by heavy foreign exchange losses
through import-spending sprees.  
