<HEADLINE> Hijacked Bulgarian Ship Sails to Somali Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, February 11 (Xinhua) - A hijacked Bulgarian ship is
sailing for the Somali port of Bosasso where the hijackers will
get off, Bulgarian Foreign Ministry Spokesman's Office said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Belize-flagged Alfa BG with 11 crew on board was hijacked
by uncontrolled Somali military units on January 13. It was being
towed by a Syrian vessel in Somali waters after having an engine
failure.
</P>
<P>
The pirates demanded 600,000 U.S. dollars for the release of
the two ships' crews. The Syrian Haramem company, which acted as
intermediary in the negotiations with the pirates, managed to
slash their demands to 130,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
The ransom was remitted to an account with a Somali bank, but
the passing of the money through several intermediaries delayed
the release of the sailors.
</P>
<P>
The ship is expected to arrive in Bosasso around midnight
Bulgarian local time where the hijackers will disembark, the
Bulgarian Embassy in the Ethiopian capital of Addis Ababa said.
</P>
<P>
The ship will then leave for the Yemeni port of Aden.
</P>
<P>
The sailors are in good health and are happy that the incident
has ended, the captain of Alfa BG said in a message conveyed via a
passing Bulgarian ship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
