<HEADLINE> Shanghai Gives List of Top 10 Stock Traders in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange
has listed its top ten stock dealers in 1997, measured by trading
volume.
</P>
<P>
Shenyin Wanguo Securities came in first, followed by the
Huaxia, Haitong, Jun'an, Nanfang, Shanghai Finance, Jiangsu,
Guotai, Fujian Xingye, and Guangdong Development companies.
</P>
<P>
Shenyin Wanguo ranked first in six categories: general trading,
A-shares, B-shares, funds, state bonds, and spot-transaction, and
re-purchasing of state bonds.
</P>
<P>
The 10 top dealers did a total of 1,736.57 billion yuan in
trading last year, accounting for nearly 30 percent of the total
volume. 
</P>
</TEXT>
