<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poland Prepared to Send Troops to Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The Polish Government said on
Wednesday that Poland is prepared to deploy appropriate supportive
troops to the Persian Gulf region if necessary.
</P>
<P>
An official statement issued by the government said the Polish
government has been following the situation in the gulf closely
since the beginning of the crisis arising out of the United
Nations weapons inspections in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Although the Polish government supports the efforts made by the
United States and other countries for a peaceful solution, it
realizes that the use of force will be realistic if all these
efforts are in vain, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
But it noted that the use of force was a last resort, and could
be justified only after the exhaustion of all political solutions
to persuade Iraq to comply with relevant resolutions adopted by
the United Nations Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that in response to a United States
request for Polish support, the Polish government had decided to
send antichemical warfare troops, a platoon or battalion strong,
to the Gulf if necessary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
