<HEADLINE> Nicaragua's Foreign Debt Reaches Seven Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Nicaragua's foreign debt
amounted to seven billion U.S. dollars at the beginning of this
month, a 10-percent increase over the end of last year, a
Nicaraguan official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Noel Ramirez, president of the Nicaraguan Central Bank, said
the foreign debt reached more than 6.4 billion dollars at the end
of last year.
</P>
<P>
Minister of External Cooperation David Robleto attributed the
rise to the increase of new projects and
non-governmental funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
