<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Ambon, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.5 on
the Richter scale jolted Ambon, capital of Indonesia's Maluku
province and its surrounding areas at 20:54 local time on
Wednesday, the Antara news agency said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was 45 km beneath the sea, Antara
quoted the Meteorological and Geophysical Office in Ambon as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The tremors panicked and forced local residents to stay
outdoors.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report of damage or casualties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
