<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Table Tennis Star Thrown out of National Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Table tennis star Yang Ying,
member of China's world women's championship team, has been thrown
out of the national squad for missing the roll call at the
training camp in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Yang, from southeast China's Jiangsu province, has been sent to
the provincial team as a punishment of her indiscipline, said head
coach Cai Zhenhua.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old Yang, who plays a fast-attacking game in the
penhold style, helped China win the team title at the world
championships in Manchester, England, last May. She also snatched
the doubles crown with world No.1 Deng Yaping.
</P>
<P>
All Chinese national team players were demanded to return to
the Beijing camp by 19:00 of February 1 after the Lunar New Year
holiday which started on January 28. Yang was three hours late
for the roll call, said Cai.
</P>
<P>
"She is complacent after the world championships," said Cai. "I
have to be fair. Everyone must return to the camp by the exact
time I demand."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese coach said Yang could make her way back to the
national team.
</P>
<P>
"If she works hard and disciplines herself, we may call her
back," Cai said.
</P>
<P>
Yang, who had complained Cai was just too tough on her, said on
Wednesday that she felt remorseful and would shape up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
