<HEADLINE> U.S. Sells Italy Anti-Aircraft Missiles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Italy will receive 735
shoulder-fired, U.S.-made Stinger air defense missiles under a
planned sale of 110 million U.S. dollars, the Defense Department
announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Italy, which already has Stringers in its inventory, will use
the missiles to update its air defense capability, a Pentagon said
in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"This proposed sale will contribute to the foreign policy and
national security objectives of the United States by improving the
military capabilities of Italy while enhancing weapon system
standardization and interoperability," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The missiles will be provided by the company of Hughes Aircraft
based in Tucson, Arizona. 
</P>
