<HEADLINE> New Grain Production Center In Northern Chinese Pastoral Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Hulun Buir League
(prefecture) in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region has become a
new grain production center, with its annual grain output
increasing 19 percent annually to 1.6 billion kg last year.
</P>
<P>
Wheat, bean, and rape seed output has gone from 1.5 billion kg
in 1996 to last year's two billion kg. The bean production base in
southern Hulun Buir provides 70 percent of Inner Mongolia's beans
with 19 percent of its land.
</P>
<P>
This has meant the league is self-sufficient in grain supply
and can even sell its surplus grain to other parts of the
country. A local agriculture official says that this is because of
greater use of capital in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Farmers have reclaimed 266,600 ha of wasteland, and improved
200,000 ha of low-yield land and dug 1,400 km of irrigation
ditches. As a result, it has 1.3 million ha of cultivated land.
</P>
<P>
The league has used 40 million yuan from abroad to build
cooking oil refineries, flour mills, and farms.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
