<HEADLINE> Guinea Holds Cameroon to 2-2 Draw in African Nations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Guinea scored two second half
goals to force a 2-2 draw against Cameroon in the fifth day of
African Cup of Nations soccer finals in Burkina Faso on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon took the lead in the eighth minute when Alphonse
Tchami blasted a shot past Guinea's goaltender Saliou Diallo.
</P>
