<HEADLINE> Japan's current account surplus up 57.4 percent in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 12 (Xinhua) - Japan's current account surplus
in December increased 57.4 percent from a year earlier to 1,295.6
billion yen (about 10 billion U.S. dollars), the finance ministry
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The nation's trade surplus jumped 35.7 percent to 1,416.9
billion yen (11.3 billion dollars) in the month, with exports
climbing 12.2 percent to 4,563.8 billion yen while imports rising
4.1 percent to 3,146.9 billion yen.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Japan's current account surplus surged 59.8 percent to
11,435.7 billion yen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
