<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Enjoy Religious Freedom, Says Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Constitution
provides religious freedom to citizens and some Westerners
accusing China of "religious persecution" do not understand the
reality in China, a high-ranking official said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
There are over 100 million religious believers in China, and
the church there has printed over 20 million copies of Bible for
them, said Ye Xiaowen, visiting Director of the Religious Affairs
Bureau under the State Council of China.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference that he knew from a friend that at a
recent Washington D.C. seminar on "Religious Persecution in China",
nor speakers or participants were aware of the figures.
</P>
<P>
Besides, he said, nobody knew that there were only 700,000
Protestant believers in China before 1949 when the People's
Republic of China was founded.
</P>
<P>
That was what happened within 150 years since the first
introduction of Protestantism into China, he added.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, he said, the number of protestant believers in
China has grown to over 10 million in the past four decades.
</P>
<P>
Ye and two Chinese religious leaders arrived in the United
States on January 29 for a visit at the invitation of U.S.
distinguished religious figure Billy Graham and Chairman of East
Gates International Rev. Nelson Graham.
</P>
<P>
The trip has taken them to Seattle, Chicago and Washington with
the last stop at New York to end on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ye said from his contacts with U.S.church leaders and
congressmen, he strongly feel that most Americans hope to have
good understanding of China and want to see growing friendship
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"That is the main stream which is irresistible," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
