<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese UN Ambassador Briefs on China's Social Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Government
has always attached great importance to coupling economic growth
with all-round social development, so as to ensure social
stability and harmony, Qin Huasun, Chinese Ambassador to the
United Nations said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 36th session of the Commission for Social
Development of the United Nations, Qin Huasun said since the
policy of reform and opening up was introduced in 1978, the
Chinese Government, by taking a series of measures to eliminate
poverty, has lifted 200 million Chinese out of poverty and thus
provided them with necessary material conditions to better enjoy
the various rights entitled to them.
</P>
<P>
Qin said, to solve the problem of the workers laid off during
the economic reconstructuring process, many cities have managed to
set up "re-employment fund", carry out "re-employment programs",
and give re-employment training to laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
Qin said the Chinese people enjoy the rights to participate in
social life. It is stipulated by the Constitution of the People's
Republic of China that all power of the People's Republic of China
belongs to the people. The People exercise their right to
participate in the discussion and running of state affairs through
the democratically-elected National People's congress and local
people's congress at various levels.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Qin said China is a country composed of people from
many ethnic groups. Therefore, ethnic unity holds the key to
social stability and social development. The Chinese Government
has instituted a system of regional autonomy in ethnic minority
areas, which respects the customs and traditions of minority
ethnic groups and opposes the discrimination and oppression of
them. On the other hand, the Chinese Government has also made
untiring efforts to help develop the economy of minority areas so
as to achieve common progress.
</P>
<P>
The Ambassador said the Chinese Government also pays much
attention to the life and development of such vulnerable groups as
the young, the elderly and the disabled by formulating policies
and regulations to ensure that those groups enjoy the equal right
to be integrated in social life and share the material and
cultural achievement of the society.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
