<HEADLINE> Dow Crosses 8,300 Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 11 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks extended a
bullish mode on Wednesday, with the Dow Jones industrial average
closing 18.94 higher to 8,314.55, the first time the most
important benchmark closed above the 8,300 point line.
</P>
<P>
This came one day after the Dow set an intraday record of
8,310.56 and reached a record close of 8,295.61 which was 115.09
up from Monday's close.
</P>
<P>
At the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE), advancing issues beat
decliners 9-8, with 1,536 up, 1,362 down and 571 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The transaction volume, however, declined to 593.86 million
shares from 641.52 million shares previously, according to
preliminary calculations.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 stock list was up 1.00 to 1,020.01
and the NYSE composite index gained 0.79 to 530.75.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nastaq composite index which rose sharply
on Tuesday, fell a slight 0.49 to close at 1,708.55.
</P>
<P>
The Russel 2000 index of smaller companies edged up 0.83 to
452.02 while the small-company dominated American Stock Exchange
composite index retreated 1.71 to 684.33. 
</P>
