<HEADLINE> Canada to Provide 20 Million Dollars to PNA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Canada said Wednesday it
will provide the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) with an aid
of 20 million U.S. dollars in 1998 to help improve the living
conditions of Palestinian refugees.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Peace Envoy Andrew Robinson announced the decision
while meeting with PNA Minister of Planning and International
Cooperation Nabil Shaath in Gaza, according to Jerusalem Media and
Communication Center (JMCC).
</P>
<P>
Shaath extended PNA's thanks to the Canadian government for the
assistance. He said the issue of the Palestinian refugees and
their return to homeland are PNA's priorities.
</P>
<P>
There are about 3.6 million Palestinian refugees in the
Palestinian self-rule areas, Lebanon, Jordan and other parts of
the world.
</P>
<P>
The return of the refugees is one of the major issues needed to
be settled between the PNA and Israel in their final status
talks. 
</P>
